I'm printing blank labels? 1.Please make sure your labels are properly loaded. The printing side is facing up. 2.Ensure your labels are direct thermal labels. 3.It's possible that the printer do not recognize the label size correctly yet.Pls calibrate the label in the printer. How to calibrate the label when change the label size? Turn the power on,hold the feed button, until you see the red light flashes 3 times then release the feed button. The printer will automatically eject paper, and after the paper is successfullyejected, the machine will automatically calibrate. When I print the label, the label is too small? Window: Go to the control panel → devices and printers→click print preferences→option→change print speed and darkness→click apply Mac: Open your file with preview. Click print→select "show details→choose the paper size you want or manage custom sizes How to start the printer? Please get the driver and how to video from the u disk to start your printing

reviews.reviewText: After reading some reviews I was a little worried about installation/setup being tricky but I plugged it right in, downloaded the driver and immediately started printing. It's literally so easy. Plus I got the green one so its super cute. Prints VERY fast!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works fine, but you have to know what you're doing
reviews.reviewText: The printer itself is excellent and works perfectly as a USB device. The wireless part is another story:- The wireless connection software you download to your phone is useless and doesn't connect properly;- There's a "diagnostics" program on the CD which lets you talk to it from a PC. This works, but you have to work for the United Nations to figure it out, because the software is pretty much experimental: some of the buttons and prompts are in Chinese, and only some of the functions work.But it's possible to get to the thing wirelessly if you try hard enough, and from there, it's possible to set a fixed IP address into it - and if you don't, then the chances are that if you power it down and back up again, it'll acquire a different address from DHCP, and the drivers for the computers are stupid enough not to be able to figure it out. But, once you get it set up properly, it works flawlessly.As a programmer myself, I found the software more amusing than annoying, but don't send one of these things to your grandma for Christmas.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Stopped printing after 20 labels, terrible wifi configuration process
reviews.reviewText: I bought this printer for it’s advertised wifi capability. I saw some reviews complaining about connectivity issues but I’m very technically adept, I work in information security for a large tech company so I ignored them. I have the unique perspective of running Windows, MacOS, Ubuntu Linux, and iOS. Let’s go into each process.Windows : Easiest setup, most supported. While the setup is the easiest it’s also somewhat involved for a printer. Their configuration app is archaic and not intuitive.MacOS : Doesn’t feel as supported as windows. The issue here is the printer configuration is somewhat hidden, selecting paper size or darkness is necessary but there’s no real instruction to do so. I had to watch their setup videos to set something up that should be intuitive and I still had to go digging through menus to find where to set the print darkness.Linux - Bare minimum support, they walk you though configuring the printer with CUPS, they include a binary to download that requires root to install so you don’t really know what the application is doing, it’s not a shell script so when it can’t find a directory it’s just spits out an error and you have no ability to change directory paths if a file lives elsewhere. Once again had to watch a setup video to get the settings situated and things still weren’t greatiOS - Terrible 4BARCODE application, it doesn’t integrate to your normal printers. You have to send the PDF to 4BARCODE if you want to print it. I can’t just select a printer from the list and the UI is awful, not intuitive, not directed at all.So after I’ve gone through setting up all my devices I start running through my labels, around the 20 label mark my printer stops printing and has a very fast blinking red light. I boxed it right back up and initiated a return. This process should not be this difficult only to have a faulty machine. Terrible.
